name ' test-intro-to-programming-lesson8-level5'
title 'Debugging Strategies'
description 'Match the strategy to when you should use it.'
question 'Code Tracing & Print Statements'
answer 'When your program runs but doesn\’t behave as expected, and you need to track what\’s happening.'
question 'Error Message Clarifications'
answer 'When your program produces errors and you need to analyze the traceback error message to find where the issue occurred.'
question 'AI Chatbot Assistance'
answer 'When you\'re confused about an error message or need help understanding a problem in your code.'
question 'Validation Testing'
answer 'When you need to check if your program produces the expected results.'

allow_multiple_attempts true
